Estax Version 1.0
Andreas Textor <textor.andreas@googlemail.com>

1) Read documentation at http://kantico.de/texray/estax.xhtml or in doc/ directory
2) Create your content XML and stylesheet (you can use the templates)
3) Run make

Estax uses Xalan (http://xml.apache.org/xalan-j/) and Xerces
(http://xerces.apache.org/xerces-j/), which are released under the
Apache Licence, and the XSLT Standard Library (http://xsltsl.sourceforge.net/).

If you have Xalan and Xerces installed locally (e.g. xalan.jar/xalan2.jar,
xercesImpl.jar, serializer.jar, xml-apis.jar for example in /usr/local/java
you can change the XALANPATH in the Makefile accordingly and delete the jars
in estax/.

